Commentary Text: Holder to du Plessis, out Caught by S Kaul!! That's a ridiculously immature shot from a man with the experience of FdP! With the required rate at a run-a-ball, he tries dragging a short ball from outside off, pace lost, with a pull, gets a massive top-edge and Kaul settles under it coming in from square leg! The settled batsmen depart, and is there a twist now? du Plessis c S Kaul b Holder 41(36) [4s-3 6s-2]

Commentary Text: Holder to Raina, out Lbw!! He's not going to review this! This has held Mr. IPL back his whole career - the old one-two. The short ball to get his weight on the backfoot, followed up by the yorker. Gets this one right on the boots, does Holder, and Raina is a little late on the flick, the last ball perhaps still playing in his mind. Misses it, and he's struck plumb in front. Doesn't bother with the review. Looks like it was crashing into the base of middle and leg to the naked eye. Raina lbw b Holder 2(3)

Commentary Text: Holder to Ruturaj Gaikwad, out Caught by Williamson! That's the first wicket at the half-way stage! Gaikwad charges down the wicket to cross-bat a length ball over mid-off, gives himself room to free the arms, nearly clears KW, but he leaps to hold onto the catch. That's first blood for SRH, and they get rid of the in-form Gaikwad! This could have come a little earlier, but these tracks aren't the easiest for newer batsmen. The game is still alive! Ruturaj Gaikwad c Williamson b Holder 45(38) [4s-4 6s-2]
